news.title: Macrotech Developers to acquire stake in three Ivanhoe entities for Rs 239.56 crore
news.para: The company will acquire 10% equity stake and other securities in Bellissimo Digital Infrastructure Development Management for Rs 14.77 crore, 33.33% equity stake and other securities in Palava Induslogic 4 for Rs 142.52 crore and 33.33% equity stake and other securities in Bellissimo In City FC Mumbai 1 for Rs 82.27 crore.

news.title: K Raheja Corp's Inorbit Malls acquires retail property for Rs 400 crore in Hubli
news.para: The mall is strategically situated on Gokul Main Road and its catchment extends to cover Hubli and Dharwad, the second largest urban region in Karnataka.

news.title: Developers in Gurugram use new TDR policy to increase saleable area
news.para: As per the policy of Haryana government, landowners whose land is acquired for development projects can receive TDR certificates from the government instead of monetary compensation.

news.title: Wave group to dilute land bank in Ghaziabad’s township
news.para: The combined areas these real estate developers will develop will be around 12 million square feet in the next few years.

news.title: Pilerne Forum challenges two sections of Goa's town planning act in high court
news.para: “The court has admitted our application, and the hearing is scheduled to take place on Thursday,” said Prakash Bandodkar, the forum’s convener. He said the forum has pleaded with the court to scrap these two sections and direct govt to formulate a new Regional Plan for the state.

news.title: Prime minister to inaugurate phase-I of Mumbai Metro three corridor in October
news.para: "The line will open to the public the day after the inauguration. We are fully prepared for the inaugural run," said a senior MMRCL official. According to sources, the inauguration is expected to take place between October 3 and 5, with October 4 being the most likely date.

news.title: Kerala government to develop 600-acre logistics parks in Vizhinjam
news.para: Awareness campaigns are being conducted in neighbourhoods such as Venganoor to inform residents about the benefits, potential for jobs and regional development of the project.

news.title: MPIDC allots 3,000 plots to beneficiaries of land pooling scheme in Indore
news.para: The proposed industrial belt sector 7 in Pithampur is being developed on more than 2,000 hectare, with a significant portion of the land, roughly 1,351 hectares, to be acquired from private landowners.

news.title: Bengaluru development body sets development fee for buildings in Shivaram Karanth layout
news.para: The fee is based on the difference between the 2018 residential plot value set by the Registration and Stamps Department and the 2024 residential plot value.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh housing board allows amalgamation of adjacent plots if owner is same
news.para: While for residential properties, joining two plots into a single unit will be allowed upon paying 2% of the reserved rates, for commercial properties, amalgamation of four plots will be allowed upon payment of 5%.

news.title: Karnataka government face hurdles to acquire 85,000 acres for satellite township projects
news.para: One project involves Karnataka Housing Board (KHB) which aims to create five theme-based townships in Solur (healthcare), Bidadi (cultural), Doddaballapur (manufacturing), Hoskote (IT), and Dabaspet (logistics). KHB needs 2,000 acres for each of these satellite towns.

news.title: REIT Association launches DBIs to provide detailed information to investors
news.para: As part of this initiative, under SEBI's guidance, three leading financial services companies- CareEdge, CAMS, and KFintech-have launched dedicated platforms to house all key information regarding REITs, assisting investors with their investment decisions.

news.title: Noida: NGT seeks response on alleged environmental violations in Jaypee Wishtown
news.para: In a recent order, a bench headed by NGT Chairperson Justice Prakash Shrivastava took note of the allegations about the township being located on the Yamuna riverbed, around 2 km from the river, under the Okhla Bird Sanctuary.

news.title: Morgan Stanley leases 1.1 million sq ft office space in Mumbai’s Goregaon
news.para: The company has leased the space spread over 16 floors of commercial tower Oberoi Commerz III for a total term of nine-and-a-half years through its India arm, Morgan Stanley Advantage Services.

news.title: Karnataka RERA faces criticism for poor enforcement in state
news.para: According to data published on the K-RERA website, only 65% of the registered housing projects are currently under construction. As of September 10, there are 6,944 registered housing projects in the state, but construction is ongoing in just 4,543 of them.

news.title: Arkade Developers IPO subscribed 29.42 times on third day
news.para: The quota for non-institutional investors garnered 58.80 times subscription while the Retail Individual Investors (RIIs) part got subscribed 33.26 times. The portion for Qualified Institutional Buyers (QIBs) received 61 per cent subscription.

news.title: Bajaj Housing Finance shares declines 4.50% after two-day sharp rally
news.para: On the NSE, shares of the firm ended lower by 4.57 per cent to close at Rs 173.19. Its market valuation also eroded by Rs 6,487.63 crore to Rs 1,44,651.58 crore.

news.title: YEIDA earns Rs 500 crore from e-auction of 45 commercial plots
news.para: While the reserve price for each plot was set at Rs 2.50 crore, amounting to a total bid price of Rs 112.50 crore, the authority secured Rs 265.14 crore through the auction— an excess of Rs 152.64 crore, or 134% above the original bid price.

news.title: Chevron leases three lakh sq ft commercial space in Bengaluru from RMZ Corporation
news.para: RMZ Corporation currently has 21 million sq ft of office projects in various stages of construction and plans to add another 30 million sq ft of office space, in the next 2-3 years to have an office portfolio of 50 million sq ft in six cities.

news.title: Godrej Capital aims for assets under management of Rs 17,000 crore by December 2024
news.para: ​Currently, the company manages an asset base of Rs 13,000 crore, and by March 2026, Godrej Capital aims to increase this figure to Rs 30,000 crore and further look for a longer-term goal of achieving an AUM of Rs 50,000 crore by March 2028, he said here.
